headline: Trump's State of the Union, Nvidia earnings, Fed: What to Watch

headline: Lowe’s Resets Corporate Structure And Payments As Valuation Risks Mount
summary: Lowe's Companies (NYSE:LOW) is cutting about 600 corporate and support roles as it reshapes its organizational structure. The company is shifting more resources toward stores and customer facing operations, with transitional support for affected employees. Lowe's is updating its 2025 retail focus around professionals and DIYers, product category mix, digital tools, and an AI driven retail playbook. A new national partnership with Affirm will offer flexible online and mobile payment options...

headline: Lowe's (NYSE:LOW) Posts Better-Than-Expected Sales In Q4 CY2025
summary: Home improvement retailer Lowe’s (NYSE:LOW) reported Q4 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 10.9% year on year to $20.58 billion. The company expects the full year’s revenue to be around $93 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.98 per share was 1.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
